By removing `onAttachedToRecyclerView` and moving the logic to a custom `attach` method, you've introduced a regression. The `attach` method is no longer called automatically when the adapter is set on a `RecyclerView`. This will lead to a `NullPointerException` because dependencies are not injected and `mLayoutInflater` in the base class is not initialized. You should reintroduce `onAttachedToRecyclerView` and call your `attach` method from there to ensure proper initialization.

```suggestion
    @Override
    public void onAttachedToRecyclerView(@NonNull RecyclerView recyclerView) {
        super.onAttachedToRecyclerView(recyclerView);
        attach(recyclerView.getContext(), recyclerView);
    }

    @Override
    public void attach(Context context, RecyclerView recyclerView) {
        super.attach(context, recyclerView);
        ((MaterialisticApplication) context.getApplicationContext()).applicationComponent.inject(this);
    }
